From: 
To: 
Cc: 
Subject: RE: order of proof meeting 
Date: Wed, 02 Jun 2021 22:32:31 +0000 
Attachments: 2021.06.02_Maxwell_Scheduling_Orderitrial_schedule).pdf 
Attached is the scheduling order for pretrial filings. 
From 
Sent: Wednesda June 2  2021 5:28 PM 
To: 
Subject: Re: order of proof meeting 
Great.IM and I are doing a brown bag for the summer interns until 1:30 on the 14th, but we should be free that 
afternoon. I'm also free the morning of the 15th. If possible and assuming you're all comfortable with it, could we meet in 
person? 
On Jun 2, 2021, at 5:20 PM ote: 
Following up on our conversation this morning, the team is free for an order of proof meeting during the following 
windows: 
•  Anytime after 12 p.m. on June 14th
•  Anytime before 12 p.m. June 15th
We chatted as a team, and we're going to be working on the RTC and a Daubert motion over the summer, as we 
discussed. Time permitting, we're likely going to work ahead on a 404(b) motion as well. 
Thanks, 
Assistant United States Attorney 
Southern District of New York 
One Saint Andrew's Plaza 
New York. NY 10007 
EFTA00028705
